  <prompt>
    Close out Phase G. (1) Write `notes/phase-g/lessons-learned.md` capturing the journey from text-field to lookup-driven design, the migration approach, what went well, what would do differently. (2) Update `docs/guides/MULTI-CONTAINER-MULTI-INDEX-OPERATOR-RUNBOOK.md` (created in task 060) to reflect Phase G changes — operators now manage indexes via the `sprk_aisearchindex` table, not App Service config. (3) Find Similar UAT — verify the existing VisualizationService Find Similar feature works across the multi-index setup (relationships traversal works when source doc and target doc are in different indexes — should be denied with a clear message, or work intra-index per existing spec). (4) Create `.claude/patterns/ai/semantic-vs-relational-views.md` — 25-line pattern pointer codifying the "files = AI Search index; documents = Dataverse views; no mixing" principle from the project's design conversations.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Project owner doing final docs + UAT pass. Familiar with the project's lessons-learned + pattern-doc conventions.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Phase G fully closed: lessons captured; operator runbook updated; Find Similar UAT'd; pattern doc landed.
  </goal>

