  <steps>
    <step order="1">Write `projects/spaarke-multi-container-multi-index-r1/notes/phase-g/lessons-learned.md`. Sections: Why Phase G (text→lookup pivot); What worked (lookup-first + text-fallback during soak); What surprised us (form-binding-as-throwaway issue; the user's clear architectural call on "no formula fields"); What we'd do differently (consider lookup design earlier in R1 spec).</step>
    <step order="2">Update `docs/guides/MULTI-CONTAINER-MULTI-INDEX-OPERATOR-RUNBOOK.md`. Add a section "Managing indexes via sprk_aisearchindex" describing: adding/removing index rows; the `sprk_isdefault` flag; relationship to BU `sprk_aisearchindexid` lookup cascade. Update the troubleshooting section: empty-table behavior + warning log location (App Insights, "DataverseAllowedIndexesProvider empty result").</step>
    <step order="3">Find Similar UAT: open a doc with `sprk_aisearchindexid` set to a specific row; trigger Find Similar in the PCF; verify it returns documents from the SAME index (intra-index by design). If a doc is moved across indexes (rare), Find Similar should return empty rather than fail — verify graceful degradation.</step>
    <step order="4">Create `.claude/patterns/ai/semantic-vs-relational-views.md`. 25-line pointer file with the core principle: "Files = AI Search semantic index; Documents = Dataverse OOB views; no mixing." Point to spec §6 + the BFF `SemanticSearchService.AssociatedOnly` path as the canonical examples.</step>
    <step order="5">Update `TASK-INDEX.md`: 111 🔲 → ✅. Mark Phase G complete in the project README.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
